  }, "That really is typical of your generation. You are really doing your own. You are not endowed with something the generation before you didn't have, but the generation before I was brought up my mother my father died when I was very young my mother would say, \"Darling, this man is taking a lot of trouble to talk to you. He was a great friend of your father,\" and I'd say I didn't like what he was saying and mother would say \"Never mind what you think, pay attention to this man, he does know what he's saying, and he's taking a lot of trouble...\" And I was continually being told, \"Never mind what you think, pay attention.\" And I was being sent to the school where they were going to really show me, and so I continually found what I was thinking a little \"out\" from what I was being taught, so I assumed that I was just a freak, and I'd have to get on with myself as a freak. I don't know how many of you have really had to think that way about yourself, but I thought, \"I've got to live with a freak.\"", mdx("span", {
